    <abstract id="aspace_c6c8d6e3f0b037580bd605ecda85030e" label="Abstract">The Jones &amp; Laughlin Steel Corporation's mill in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, began producing steel in 1886 and had facilities on both banks of the Monongahela River.  This collection includes personnel cards for employees of Jones &amp; Laughlin's plant in south side Pittsburgh.</abstract>
    <langmaterial>
      <language langcode="eng">English</language>
.    </langmaterial>
